TY  - JOUR
T1  - An Extension of the Gomory Mixed-Integer Algorithm to Mixed-Discrete Variables
AU  - Dalton, Robert E.
AU  - Llewellyn, Robert W.
Y1  - 1966/03/01
PY  - 1966
DA  - 1966/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.12.7.569
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.12.7.569
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 569
EP  - 575
VL  - 12
IS  - 7
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - The methods of R. E. Gomory for the iterative solution of the mixed-integer linear programming problem are extended directly to the case where some or all of the variables are nonuniformly discrete, i.e., they are restricted to assume values from certain specified sets of unequally-spaced constants. The algorithm presented is shown to converge in a finite number of steps for a discrete-valued objective function.
AB  - The methods of R. E. Gomory for the iterative solution of the mixed-integer linear programming problem are extended directly to the case where some or all of the variables are nonuniformly discrete, i.e., they are restricted to assume values from certain specified sets of unequally-spaced constants. The algorithm presented is shown to converge in a finite number of steps for a discrete-valued objective function.
