JO  - Management Science
SP  - 576
EP  - 587
VL  - 12
IS  - 7
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - An algorithm is presented for the solution of mixed integer programming problems. The method was developed to solve primarily those programming problems which contain a large number of continuous variables in addition to a few variables that are restricted to discrete values. The algorithm solves a continuous, non-integer constrained problem first. Subsequently, a search for the optimum integer solution is made on the basis of those changes in the value of the objective function that are produced by activating integer constraints.
AB  - An algorithm is presented for the solution of mixed integer programming problems. The method was developed to solve primarily those programming problems which contain a large number of continuous variables in addition to a few variables that are restricted to discrete values. The algorithm solves a continuous, non-integer constrained problem first. Subsequently, a search for the optimum integer solution is made on the basis of those changes in the value of the objective function that are produced by activating integer constraints.
